{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cac481df-53b7-4d0e-bf31-901f1d2e2dc4","content":"Here's how to migrate from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) while keeping TRX reports and code coverage:\n\n### 1. Update your test projects\n\nIn each `.csproj`, add:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nEnsure you're on **MSTest 3.x+** (`Microsoft.Testing.Platform` is bundled).\n\n### 2. Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\nMTP-based tests are native executables, so `VSTest@3` is no longer needed. Use the `DotNetCoreCLI@2` task (or a plain script):\n\n```yaml\n# Before (remove this)\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblies: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=TestResults.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\nOr equivalently as a script:\n\n```yaml\n- script: >-\n    dotnet test **/*Tests.csproj\n    --configuration Release\n    --logger \"trx;LogFileName=TestResults.trx\"\n    --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n### 3. Publish TRX results\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n```\n\n### 4. Publish code coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n> If your coverage collector produces `.coverage` files instead of Cobertura, add the `coverlet.collector` NuGet package and use `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` to get Cobertura XML directly.\n\n### Key differences from VSTest@3\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | MTP (`dotnet test`) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Test discovery | Scans DLLs | Builds & runs projects |\n| TRX output | Built-in | `--logger trx` flag |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` toggle | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| Result publishing | Automatic | Separate `PublishTestResults@2` step |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4c0ac0ab-e263-4640-b91e-926e554ea46e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears empty. This seems like a general knowledge question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":786,"requestId":"BD0A:2DE6FB:1CF9D52:20AB2CB:6A07C4C8"},"id":"36273e1c-901c-417c-9884-217cc8d9b13d","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:13:59.479Z","parentId":"210f2e94-af27-4782-a297-8052e0d1d1ef"}
